description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you keen to branch out into a specialist nurse post looking after colorectal cancer patients with an interest in Enhanced Recovery After Surgery (ERAS).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you have commitment to developing your skills in colorectal nursing and taking on more responsibility and autonomy in practice?.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic and highly motivated nurse with excellent communication skills and a passion for this specialist area of nursing, for a 12 month secondment, band 6 post. 37.5 hours per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Colorectal team have recently completed a 2 year Macmillan project developing the colorectal ERAS programme, the successful post holder will be at the forefront of continuing this service with educational links both in secondary and primary care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information or an informal visit, please contact the colorectal nursing team on 01270 612047&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be held on Monday 7th December 2020&lt;/p&gt;
